      "text": "Issues\n\n- Home\n- Market Rules\n- Issues\n\n## NPRR1096\n\n- Summary\n- Action\n- Voting Record\n- Background\n- Key Documents\n\n#### Summary\n\n12/09/2022\n\nSections 2.1, 3.17.3, and 8.1.1.2\n\n06/09/2023\n\nAll remaining sections\n\n| Title | Require Sustained Two-Hour Capability for ECRS and Four-Hour Capability for Non-Spin |\n| --- | --- |\n| Next Group |\n| Next Step |\n| Status | Approved on 05/12/2022 |\n| Effective Dates |\n\n#### Action\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Action Taken | Next Steps |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 05/12/2022 | PUCT | Approved |\n| 04/28/2022 | BOARD | Recommended for Approval | PUCT for consideration |\n| 03/30/2022 | TAC | Recommended for Approval | Board for consideration |\n| 03/09/2022 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | TAC for consideration |\n| 02/09/2022 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | PRS for Impact Analysis consideration |\n| 10/14/2021 | PRS | Deferred/Tabled | PRS for consideration |\n\n#### Voting Record\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Motion | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 05/12/2022 | PUCT | To approve NPRR1096 and accompanying ERCOT Market Impact Statement as presented in Project No. 52934, Review of Rules Adopted by the Independent Organization |\n| 04/28/2022 | BOARD | To recommend approval of NPRR1096 as recommended by TAC in the 3/30/22 TAC Report | Passed |\n| 03/30/2022 | TAC | To recommend approval of NPRR1096 as recommended by PRS in the 3/9/22 PRS Report | Passed |\n| 03/09/2022 | PRS | To endorse and forward to TAC the 2/9/22 PRS Report and Revised Impact Analysis for NPRR1096 with a recommended priority of 2022 and rank of 2650 | Passed |\n| 02/09/2022 | PRS | To recommend approval of NPRR1096 as amended by the 11/3/21 ERCOT comments | Passed |\n| 10/14/2021 | PRS | To table NPRR1096 and refer the issue to ROS and WMS | Passed |\n\n#### Background\n\n| Status: | Approved |\n| --- | --- |\n| Date Posted: | Sep 28, 2021 |\n| Sponsor: | ERCOT |\n| Urgent: | No |\n| Sections: | 2.1, 3.17.3, 3.17.4, 8.1.1.2, 8.1.1.3.3, and 8.1.1.3.4 |\n| Description: | This Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) requires Resources that provide ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for two consecutive hours and/or Non-Spinning Reserve (Non-Spin) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for four consecutive hours. Additionally, this NPRR also requires ERCOT to conduct unannounced tests on Energy Storage Resources (ESRs) that are providing ECRS and/or Non-Spin in Real-Time. |\n| Reason: | Addresses current operational issues |\n\n#### Key Documents\n\n1096NPRR-01 Require Sustained Six Hour Capability for ECRS and Non-Spin 092821\n\nSep 28, 2021 - docx - 53.9 KB\n\n1096NPRR-02 Impact Analysis 092821\n\nSep 28, 2021 - docx - 30.3 KB\n\n1096NPRR-03 PRS Ballot 101421\n\nOct 15, 2021 - xls - 114.5 KB\n\n1096NPRR-04 PRS Report 101421\n\nOct 15, 2021 - docx - 54.8 KB\n\n1096NPRR-05 ERCOT Comments 110321\n\nNov 3, 2021 - docx - 40.9 KB\n\n1096NPRR-06 ROS Comments 110521\n\nNov 5, 2021 - docx - 22.6 KB\n\n1096NPRR-07 WMS Comments 110821\n\nNov 8, 2021 - docx - 22.7 KB\n\n1096NPRR-08 HEN Comments 111021\n\nNov 10, 2021 - docx - 41.6 KB\n\n1096NPRR-09 Sierra Club Comments 111121\n\nNov 11, 2021 - docx - 23.6 KB\n\n1096NPRR-10 Enel Green Power Comments 120721\n\nDec 8, 2021 - docx - 22.9 KB\n\n1096NPRR-11 Joint Commenters Comments 010522\n\nJan 5, 2022 - docx - 45.6 KB\n\n1096NPRR-12 ROS Ballot 010622\n\nJan 12, 2022 - xls - 110.5 KB\n\n1096NPRR-13 ROS Comments 011222\n\nJan 12, 2022 - docx - 40.2 KB\n\n1096NPRR-14 TAEBA Comments 011222\n\nJan 12, 2022 - docx - 23.1 KB\n\n1096NPRR-15 ERCOT Comments 020122\n\nFeb 1, 2022 - docx - 23.4 KB\n\n1096NPRR-16 WMS Ballot 020222\n\nFeb 7, 2022 - xls - 140 KB\n\n1096NPRR-17 WMS Comments 020722\n\nFeb 7, 2022 - docx - 23.2 KB\n\n1096NPRR-18 KCE Comments 020722\n\nFeb 7, 2022 - docx - 47.3 KB\n\n1096NPRR-19 PRS Ballot 020922\n\nFeb 14, 2022 - xls - 115.5 KB\n\n1096NPRR-20 PRS Report 020922\n\nFeb 14, 2022 - docx - 57 KB\n\n1096NPRR-21 Revised Impact Analysis 022822\n\nFeb 28, 2022 - docx - 30.5 KB\n\n1096NPRR-22 PRS Ballot 030922\n\nMar 10, 2022 - xls - 111 KB\n\n1096NPRR-23 PRS Report 030922\n\nMar 10, 2022 - docx - 57.4 KB\n\n1096NPRR-24 Jupiter Power Comments 032822\n\nMar 28, 2022 - docx - 246.6 KB\n\n1096NPRR-25 TAC Ballot 033022\n\nApr 1, 2022 - xls - 112 KB\n\n1096NPRR-26 TAC Report 033022\n\nApr 1, 2022 - docx - 58.2 KB\n\n1096NPRR-27 Board Report 042822\n\nMay 2, 2022 - docx - 58.3 KB\n\n1096NPRR-28 PUCT Report 051222\n\nMay 17, 2022 - docx - 58.6 KB\n\n##### Related Content\n\n###### On this site",
